text: Wang Jian (), also known as Wang Chien, is a female Chinese former international table tennis player. ==Table tennis career== She won two bronze medals at the 1961 World Table Tennis Championships in the women's doubles with Hu Keming and women's singles. Two years later she won two more bronze medals at the 1963 World Table Tennis Championships in the Corbillon Cup (women's team) and women's doubles with Qiu Zhonghui. ==See also== * List of table tennis players * List of World Table Tennis Championships medalists ==References== Category:Chinese female table tennis players Category:Table tennis players from Beijing Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:World Table Tennis Championships medalists
